#week-title("Two", "The Ethics of Alchemy: Sincerity & Service")

=== Core Teaching

The ethics of alchemical medicine are central to its efficacy. Personal greed
has no place in this Art. As Frater Albertus states: "The aim of all true Adepts
is to help relieve a suffering mankind in its physical and spiritual misery."

The alchemical oath taken in Week 1 (Silence, Sincerity, Service) is now applied
to the medicine itself. It is given with full transparency about its nature, and
only to those who have demonstrated preparation.

#doctrine[
  _"A non-acceptance of the aim to serve mankind excludes one automatically from
  the circle of Adepts."_
  #align(right)[— AH, adapted]
]

=== Topics This Week

- The link between ethics and efficacy
- Transparency in sharing preparations
- The exclusion of personal greed

#inner-work[
  *Reviewing the Oath*

  Review your Declaration of Intent from Month 1, Week 1. How has your
  understanding of "service" changed over the past ten months? Are you still
  holding onto personal vanity or the desire for approval?

  Write an honest one-paragraph assessment of your current sincerity. This is
  not for the Headmaster, but for your own Stone.
]

